<Base title="Cineslate — Support" doc>
  <nav><a href="/cineslate/">← Cineslate</a></nav>
  <h1>Support</h1>

  <h2>Get in touch</h2>
  <p>Email us at <a href="mailto:support@sunpebblelabs.com">support@sunpebblelabs.com</a> —
     we usually reply within two days. Or message us on <a href="https://t.me/sunpebble">Telegram</a>.</p>

  <h2>Where is my library?</h2>
  <p>Everything you mark as Watching, Upcoming, Watchlist, or History lives only on your device.
     Delete the app and it's gone; we never have it. See the
     <a href="/cineslate/privacy/">Privacy Policy</a>.</p>

  <h2>Connecting Plex</h2>
  <p>Open Settings → Plex and sign in. Cineslate talks directly to Plex's official API to list and
     play titles you already own. Your Plex token is stored securely in the device Keychain and sent
     only to Plex.</p>

  <h2>Subtitles</h2>
  <p>Cineslate can fetch subtitles via OpenSubtitles. Connect it in Settings to pick a language per
     playback; subtitles are streamed on demand and not stored.</p>

  <h2>Where do posters and cast come from?</h2>
  <p>From TMDB. Cineslate makes read-only requests to their public API; no personal data is sent.</p>
</Base>
